MGM rented Dodger Stadium in Los Angeles for the fictitious Santa Fe Race scenes in &quot;Spinout.&quot; Three elderly ladies found out that Elvis was there and they traveled to L.A. in hopes of seeing him. They made their way into the stadium and walked all around the track, unaware that the scene was being filmed where cars were going by at over 100 mph. Elvis ran to where the ladies were standing and pulled them off the track, knocking himself over in the process.
Elvis found himself on top of one of the women, and he quickly got up and apoligized. The ladies realized Elvis had just saved them form being mangled, and they jumped all over him in thanks. Elvis was extremely amused; he told them that he would not be able to live with himself if anything happened to them.
Elvis made the ladies promise to sit in the bleachers and stay out of the way. They agreed, but only if he would give each of them his autograph. Elvis replied, &quot;What a small price to pay, to save you young ladies.&quot;

